The paper deals with the spread of an SI process on a known graph, which is a topic in the field of network science and graph theory. The paper also discusses the use of limited resources to control the spread of the epidemic, which is a problem in optimization and control theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the study of algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests the categories cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of information theory to model observation uncertainty, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and machine learning techniques, which suggests the category cs.LG (Machine Learning).
